{title: Song with Chorus}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Standing at the [G]crossroads, [Am]wondering which [F]way
[C]Left or right it [G]doesn't matter [F]anyway
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_chorus}
[F]Come on, [C]come on, [G]let it [Am]go
[F]Come on, [C]come on, [G]let it flow
[F]Every river [C]finds the [G]sea
[F]Every [G]heart will [C]be set free
{end_of_chorus}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[C]Walking through the [G]shadows, [Am]searching for the [F]light
[C]Every step I'm [G]closer to the [F]other side
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_chorus}
[F]Come on, [C]come on, [G]let it [Am]go
[F]Come on, [C]come on, [G]let it flow
[F]Every river [C]finds the [G]sea
[F]Every [G]heart will [C]be set free
{end_of_chorus}
